      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/32/16",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لَهُ اَلرَّجُلُ اَلْفَقِيرُ يُهْدِي إِلَيَّ اَلْهَدِيَّةَ يَتَعَرَّضُ لِمَا عِنْدِي فَآخُذُهَا وَ لاَ أُعْطِيهِ شَيْئاً أَ يَحِلُّ لِي قَالَ \"نَعَمْ هِيَ لَكَ حَلاَلٌ وَ لَكِنْ لاَ تَدَعْ أَنْ تُعْطِيَهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4081 - It is narrated from Ishaq ibn Ammar, who said:\nI asked Imam (as) about a poor man who gives me a gift, hoping to receive something from me in return. Is it permissible for me to accept it without giving him anything?\nImam (as) said: \"Yes, it is permissible for you, and it is lawful for you. However, do not neglect giving him something.\""
        ]
      }
    },
